.jpg|thumb|Sony's [[PlayStation Portable]] signified the company's debut in the handheld market. ''[[Forbes]]'' editor Penelope Patsuris noted \"The competition marks the first time that a company with real clout has challenged the lock that Nintendo has had on handheld gaming for 15 years.\"<ref name=\"Forbes\">{{Cite web| last = Patsuris| first = Penelope| title = Sony PSP Vs. Nintendo DS| work = [[Forbes]]| date = June 7, 2004| url = https://www.forbes.com/2004/06/07/cx_pp_0607mondaymatchup.html| accessdate = November 4, 2013| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131101213513/http://www.forbes.com/2004/06/07/cx_pp_0607mondaymatchup.html| archive-date = November 1, 2013| url-status = live}}</ref>]]\n\n<center>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Million-selling handheld game consoles\n! scope=\"col\" |Platform\n! scope=\"col\" |Firm\n! scope=\"col\" |Released{{ref label|Release sources|2|2}}\n! scope=\"col\" data-sort-type=\"number\"| Units sold\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\"     | {{abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n|[[Nintendo DS]]\n|style=\"background:#FFE8E8;\" |[[Nintendo]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"  |[[2004 in video games|2004]]\n|style=\"text-align:right\"    |154.02&nbsp;million\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"  |<ref name=nintendosales/>\n|-\n|[[Game Boy]], [[Game Boy Color]]\n|style=\"background:#FFE8E8;\"|[[Nintendo]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" |[[1989 in video games|1989]], [[1998 in video games|1998]]\n|style=\"text-align:right\"    |118.69&nbsp;million\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"  |{{efn|group=note|name=GB and GBC}}\n|-\n|[[Game Boy Advance]]\n|style=\"background:#FFE8E8;\" |[[Nintendo]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"  |[[2001 in video games|2001]]\n|style=\"text-align:right\"    |81.51&nbsp;million\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"  |<ref name=nintendosales/>\n|-\n|[[PlayStation Portable]]\n|style=\"background:#E4E4FF\"  |[[Sony]]\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"  |[[2004 in video games|2004]]\n|style=\"text-align:right\"    |80\u2013